data.chText: 赞扬；称赞
data.enText: a remark that expresses praise or admiration of sb

data.chText: 对某人表示赞扬
data.enText: to pay sb a compliment (= to praise them for sth)

data.chText: “您是能理解这个问题的，因为您年纪大那么多。”“就当你这是夸奖吧！”
data.enText: ‘You understand the problem because you're so much older.’ ‘I'll take that as a compliment !’

data.chText: 获聘请做这项工作是一项极大的荣誉。
data.enText: It's a great compliment to be asked to do the job.

data.chText: 照样回敬
data.enText: to return the compliment (= to treat sb in the same way as they have treated you)

data.chText: 致意；问候；祝贺
data.enText: polite words or good wishes, especially when used to express praise and admiration

data.chText: 请向厨师代为致意！
data.enText: My compliments to the chef!

data.chText: 谨致节日的祝贺！（圣诞节或新年时的贺词）
data.enText: Compliments of the season! (= for Christmas or the New Year)

data.chText: 请接受经理送的鲜花。
data.enText: Please accept these flowers with the compliments of (= as a gift from) the manager.

data.chText: 赞美；称赞；钦佩
data.enText: to tell sb that you like or admire sth they have done, their appearance, etc.

data.chText: 她夸奖他德语棒极了。
data.enText: She complimented him on his excellent German.

data.chText: 这两个词拼写相似，但意义完全不同。compliment指赞美、敬佩：
data.enText: These words have similar spellings but completely different meanings. If you compliment someone, you say something very nice to them.

data.chText: 她夸奖我的英语好。
data.enText: She complimented me on my English.

data.chText: complement表示相辅相成、相配合：
data.enText: If one thing complements another, the two things work or look better because they are together.

data.chText: 不同的味道搭配在一起，可口极了。
data.enText: The different flavours complement each other perfectly.

data.chText: 上述词的形容词亦常混淆。
data.enText: The adjectives are also often confused. Complimentary :

data.chText: 她对我的英语赞赏有加。
data.enText: She made some very complimentary remarks about my English.

data.chText: 该词亦含免费赠送之意：
data.enText: It can also mean ‘free’.

data.chText: 我们房间里有一篮免费赠送的水果。
data.enText: There was a complimentary basket of fruit in our room.
Complementary :

data.chText: 队员技术不同但能互补。
data.enText: The team members have different but complementary skills.

ex.enText: The boss paid her a compliment because of her diligence.

ex.chText: 能和德国战车乐队相提并论是极大的荣耀。
ex.enText: Being compared to Rammstein is a great compliment.

ex.chText: 他的所有客人都对他赞不绝口。
ex.enText: All his guests paid him extravagant compliments.

ex.chText: 对她说些恭维话没有坏处。
ex.enText: You can do no harm by paying her compliments.

synonyms.bx: 侧重于客气和礼貌的赞扬，有时含恭维之意。

ex.chText: 她的新发现受到报纸的赞扬。
ex.enText: Her new discovery received accolades from the papers.

ex.chText: 他很享受作为“中国人的朋友”而获得的双方的赞誉。
ex.enText: He enjoys the double-edged accolade of being a 'friend of China'.

ex.chText: 她获得了音乐界的最高奖项。
ex.enText: She received the highest accolades in the music business.

ex.chText: 她的嘉许就是我所能得到的最高赞赏。
ex.enText: Her approval was the highest accolade that I could have received.

synonyms.bx: 指因某种成就而受到的赞誉或奖励。

ex.chText: 消防人员中有3位因表现英勇而受到表彰。
ex.enText: Three of the firefighters received commendations for their bravery.

ex.chText: 地方政府给他们颁发了嘉奖令。
ex.enText: The local government issued an order of commendation to them.

ex.chText: 他的行为赢得了首相的赞赏。
ex.enText: His conduct earned the commendation of the prime minister.

synonyms.bx: 尤指对勇敢或很成功的人的赞扬，通常后接介词 for。

ex.chText: 她因乐于助人而受到老师的表扬。
ex.enText: She was praised by her teacher for being ready to help others.

ex.chText: 州长称赞了他的大无畏行为。
ex.enText: The governor praised him for his act of great bravery.

ex.chText: 他为提高个税起征点的决定拍手叫好。
ex.enText: He applauded the decision to raise the income tax threshold.

ex.chText: 她的宽宏大量应当受到赞许。
ex.enText: She should be applauded for her generosity.

synonyms.bx: 指强烈赞成、认同某个想法、计划等。

ex.chText: 那位参议员因热心公益事业而受到称赞。
ex.enText: The senator was commended for his public-spirited action.
His work has been highly commended.

synonyms.bx: 词义同 praise，但多用于正式文体。

ex.chText: 我的男朋友称赞我的新耳环。
ex.enText: My boyfriend complimented me on my new earrings.

ex.chText: 甚至连他的外教也夸奖他的法语棒极了。
ex.enText: Even his foreign teacher complimented him on his excellent French.

synonyms.bx: 指说好听的话，含恭维之意，多用于 compliment sb on sth 的结构中。

tr: a remark (or act) expressing praise and admiration
say something to someone that expresses praise
example: He complimented her on her last physics paper

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /'kɒmplɪment/. The noun is pronounced /'kɒmplɪmənt/. 动词读作 /'kɒmplɪment/。名词读作 /'kɒmplɪmənt/。

value.def: A compliment is a polite remark that you say to someone to show that you like their appearance, appreciate their qualities, or approve of what they have done.

example.ex: You can do no harm by paying a woman compliments...
example.tran: 对女人说些恭维话没有坏处。

example.ex: 'Well done, Cassandra,' Crook said. She blushed, but accepted the compliment with good grace.
example.tran: “干得好，卡桑德拉。”克鲁克说。她脸一下子红了，但还是很有风度地接受了恭维。

value.def: If you compliment someone, you pay them a compliment.

example.ex: They complimented me on the way I looked each time they saw me...
example.tran: 每次见到我，他们都称赞我的外貌。

example.ex: Firstly I compliment you on most of your excellent Spring issue of 'Triangle'.
example.tran: 首先，让我来夸几句，你们《三角迷踪》春季号的大部分内容都非常精彩。

value.def: If you consider something that a person says or does as a compliment, it convinces you of your own good qualities, or that the person appreciates you.

example.ex: We consider it a compliment to be called 'conservative'...
example.tran: 我们认为被称作“保守分子”是对我们的一种赞赏。

example.ex: It's obvious he's worried about us and I'm taking it as a compliment.
example.tran: 显然他担心我们，我把这当做一种赞美。

value.def: You can refer to your compliments when you want to express thanks, good wishes, or respect to someone in a formal way.

example.ex: Give my compliments to your lovely wife when you write home.
example.tran: 写信回家的时候，代我问候你可爱的妻子。

gramarinfo.label: usu poss N, oft N <l>to</l> n

value.def: If you say that someone returns the compliment, you mean that they do the same thing to someone else as that person has done to them.

example.ex: The actors have entertained us so splendidly during this weekend, I think it's time we returned the compliment.
example.tran: 这周末演员们给我们带来了精彩的演出，我觉得我们该回请他们了。

value.def: If you say that you are giving someone something with your compliments, you are saying in a polite and fairly formal way that you are giving it to them, especially as a gift or a favour.

example.ex: Please give this to your boss with my compliments...
example.tran: 请把这个给你的老板，算是我的一点心意。

example.ex: On my bedside table awaited, with the compliments of the management, an appetizing breakfast.
example.tran: 一份让人垂涎的早餐摆在我的床头桌上，那是管理人员的一点小意思。

value.tran: (尤指赠送礼物或给予帮助时)…敬赠，请接受…的敬意

trans: 称赞某人的…；在…方面称赞某人
